<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>home</title>

  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:wght@400;500;600&family=Quicksand:wght@400;500;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

  <style>
    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #ffd9e8, #ffeef5);
      color: #5b3142;
      font-family: 'Quicksand', sans-serif;
      overflow-x: hidden;
    }

    .sparkle {
      position: fixed;
      font-size: 18px;
      opacity: 0.45;
      pointer-events: none;
      animation: float 6s ease-in-out infinite;
    }

    .s1 { top: 7%; left: 8%; }
    .s2 { top: 18%; right: 10%; animation-delay: 1s; }
    .s3 { top: 42%; left: 5%; animation-delay: 2s; }
    .s4 { top: 60%; right: 7%; animation-delay: 3s; }
    .s5 { bottom: 12%; left: 12%; animation-delay: 4s; }
    .s6 { bottom: 18%; right: 15%; animation-delay: 5s; }

    @keyframes float {
      0%, 100% { transform: translateY(0px); }
      50% { transform: translateY(-10px); }
    }

    header {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 60px 20px 30px;
    }

    h1 {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
      font-size: 4rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 1px;
    }

    .subtitle {
      margin-top: 10px;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-style: italic;
    }

    .intro {
      max-width: 720px;
      margin: 0 auto 30px;
      text-align: center;
      line-height: 1.8;
      padding: 0 20px;
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .layout {
      width: 92%;
      max-width: 1250px;
      margin: 0 auto 70px;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(12, 1fr);
      gap: 24px;
      align-items: start;
    }

    .card {
      background: rgba(255, 248, 251, 0.92);
      border: 1.5px solid #efabc4;
      border-radius: 22px;
      padding: 16px;
      box-shadow: 0 10px 25px rgba(155, 92, 119, 0.12);
      transition: transform 0.25s ease, box-shadow 0.25s ease;
    }

    .card:hover {
      transform: translateY(-4px);
      box-shadow: 0 14px 30px rgba(155, 92, 119, 0.18);
    }

    .card img {
      width: 100%;
      display: block;
      border-radius: 16px;
      margin-top: 12px;
      object-fit: cover;
    }

    .card h2 {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
      font-size: 2rem;
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    .card p {
      margin: 10px 0 0;
      line-height: 1.7;
      font-size: 0.98rem;
    }

    .me {
      grid-column: span 5;
      transform: rotate(-1.2deg);
    }

    .biology {
      grid-column: span 4;
      transform: rotate(1deg);
    }

    .drinks {
      grid-column: span 3;
      transform: rotate(-1deg);
    }

    .butterfly {
      grid-column: span 4;
      transform: rotate(1.2deg);
    }

    .cat1 {
      grid-column: span 4;
      transform: rotate(-1.3deg);
    }

    .cat2 {
      grid-column: span 4;
      transform: rotate(1deg);
    }

    .note {
      grid-column: span 12;
      text-align: center;
      background: transparent;
      border: none;
      box-shadow: none;
      padding-top: 8px;
    }

    .note p {
      max-width: 700px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.9;
    }

    footer {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 10px 20px 50px;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: #7a5262;
    }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .layout {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }

      .me, .biology, .drinks, .butterfly, .cat1, .cat2, .note {
        grid-column: span 1;
        transform: none;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 3rem;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="sparkle s1">✿</div>
  <div class="sparkle s2">♡</div>
  <div class="sparkle s3">⋆</div>
  <div class="sparkle s4">✿</div>
  <div class="sparkle s5">♡</div>
  <div class="sparkle s6">⋆</div>

  <header>
    <h1>pieces of me</h1>
    <div class="subtitle">a homepage made out of the things i love most</div>
  </header>

  <div class="intro">
    this space is soft and a little scattered, like a scrapbook left open.
    i wanted it to hold things that feel like me:
    biology slides, butterflies, my cats, little memories, and the pink kind of world i like living in.
  </div>

  <main class="layout">
    <section class="card me">
      <h2>me</h2>
      <p>
        i wanted this page to feel personal instead of formal.
        something more like a memory board than an introduction.
        i love softness, light, pretty details, and collecting small things that feel meaningful.
      </p>
      <img src="IMG_6481.jpg" alt="Portrait photo" />
    </section>

    <section class="card biology">
      <h2>biology</h2>
      <p>
        i love biology because it makes the world feel intricate and alive.
        looking through a microscope feels like finding another hidden version of life,
        something delicate and beautiful that most people never stop to look at.
      </p>
      <img src="IMG_6651.jpeg" alt="Biology microscope image" />
    </section>

    <section class="card drinks">
      <h2>small memories</h2>
      <p>
        i also wanted to include moments that feel fun and real.
        not everything has to be serious to matter.
        sometimes a memory is just a color, a drink, a night out, or a feeling.
      </p>
      <img src="IMG_9172.jpeg" alt="Drinks held in glasses" />
    </section>

    <section class="card butterfly">
      <h2>butterflies</h2>
      <p>
        butterflies feel like a mix of art and biology, which is probably why i love them.
        this one feels almost unreal, like something fragile enough to disappear if you look away too fast.
      </p>
      <img src="IMG_7529.jpeg" alt="Butterfly resting on a hand" />
    </section>

    <section class="card cat1">
      <h2>my cats</h2>
      <p>
        my cats are one of the easiest ways to describe home.
        they make everything softer, quieter, and sweeter.
        i wanted them here because they are part of my everyday life.
      </p>
      <img src="IMG_7303.jpeg" alt="One of my cats sleeping" />
    </section>

    <section class="card cat2">
      <h2>christmas + home</h2>
      <p>
        my birthday is on christmas, so that time of year has always felt extra personal to me.
        lights, warmth, decorations, and my cat in the tree all somehow feel like one memory.
      </p>
      <img src="IMG_7379 (1).JPG" alt="Cat sitting in a Christmas tree" />
    </section>

    <section class="card note">
      <p>
        this homepage is less of a profile and more of a collection:
        a pink space for living things, favorite details, and pieces of life that feel beautiful to keep.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer>
    made with things i love ♡
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
